origQuery.query: select distinct t1.service_type_code from services as t1 join organizations as t2 on t1.organization_id = t2.organization_id where t2.organization_details = ' denesik and sons party '
select organisations.location , persons.first_name from persons join organisations on persons.organisation_id = organisations.id
select organisations.id , count ( persons.* ) from persons join organisations on persons.organisation_id = organisations.id group by organisations.id
select distinct participants_types.* from participants join participants_types on participants.participant_type_code = participants_types.code where participants.id > = 1124
select t2.first_name , t2.last_name , t2.actor_id from film_actor as t1 join actor as t2 on t1.actor_id = t2.actor_id group by t2.actor_id order by count ( * ) desc limit 1

select participants_types.code , participants_types.description , participants.address , participants.contact_email , participants.id from participants join participants_types on participants.participant_type_code = participants_types.code
select cases_actors.* from cases_actors join actors on cases_actors.actor_id = actors.id where actors.last_name not like ' % katie % '
select distinct genres.id , genres.name from games_genres join games on games_genres.game_id = games.id join genres on games_genres.genre_id = genres.id where games.age_rating = ' 4 + '
select players.id , players_attributes.overall_rating from players_attributes join players on players_attributes.player_id = players.id where players.height = 188
select cases_actors.* from cases_actors join actors on cases_actors.actor_id = actors.id where actors.last_name = ' barbara ' or actors.first_name = ' barbara '
select count ( * ) from home_game as t1 join park as t2 on t1.park_id = t2.park_id where t1.year = 1908 and t2.park_name = ' columbia park ' ;
select participants_types.code from participants_types where participants_types.code ! = ' wsl226 '
select cases.id , count ( cases_actors.* ) from cases_actors join cases on cases_actors.case_id = cases.id group by cases.id having count ( cases_actors.* ) < = 20
select count ( player_id ) from player_college where year = "2018" and college_id = "texas"
select t2.title , t2.film_id , t2.description from film_actor as t1 join film as t2 on t1.film_id = t2.film_id group by t2.film_id order by count ( * ) desc limit 1
select gtype from video_games group by gtype order by count ( * ) desc
select participants.contact_email , participants.name from participants where participants.id ! = 1200
select first_name , last_name from actor group by first_name , last_name order by count ( * ) desc limit 1
select * from players where players.height < 203
select total_passengers from station where station_id = "1" or station_id = "2"
select distinct posts_types.name from posts join posts_types on posts.post_type_id = posts_types.id where posts.answers_count < 28
select posts.id , sum ( tags.tagging_count ) from posts_tags join posts on posts_tags.post_id = posts.id join tags on posts_tags.tag_id = tags.id group by posts.id
select station_id , location , manager_name from gas_station order by open_year
select long , avg ( t2.duration ) from station as t1 join trip as t2 on t1.id = t2.start_station_id group by t2.start_station_id
select location , count ( * ) from gas_station group by location order by count ( * )
select network_name , count ( * ) from station as t1 join route as t2 on t1.id = t2.station_id group by t2.station_id order by count ( * ) asc
select distinct disciplines.* from employees join disciplines on employees.discipline_code = disciplines.code where employees.id < = 795
select disciplines.name , disciplines.description from disciplines where disciplines.code ! = 389
select t2.school_name , t1.budgeted , t1.invested from budget as t1 join school as t2 on t1.school_id = t2.school_id where t1.year > = 2002
select t2.railway_id , t1.builder from railway as t1 join train as t2 on t1.railway_id = t2.railway_id group by t2.railway_id order by count ( * ) desc limit 1
select t2.station_id from train as t1 join route as t2 on t1.id = t2.train_id group by t2.train_id order by count ( * ) desc limit 3
select semester , year from takes group by semester , year order by count ( * ) limit 1
select distinct t1.name from student as t1 join takes as t2 on t1.id = t2.id where year = 2009 or year = 2010
select denomination , count ( * ) from school group by denomination order by count ( * ) desc
select count ( * ) from teams where teams.short_name = ' lug '
select t2.name , t1.team_id_winner from postseason as t1 join team as t2 on t1.team_id_winner = t2.team_id_br where t1.year = 2008 group by t1.team_id_winner order by count ( * ) asc limit 1 ;
select * from teams where teams.fifa_id = teams.id order by teams.id asc
select t1.name_first , t1.name_last , count ( * ) from player as t1 join manager_award as t2 on t1.player_id = t2.player_id group by t2.player_id order by count ( * ) desc limit 1
select * from participants join organisations on participants.organisation_code = organisations.code
select distinct organisations.* from participants join organisations on participants.organisation_code = organisations.code where participants.id < = 1155
select t1.name_first , t1.name_last , count ( * ) from player as t1 join manager_award as t2 on t1.player_id = t2.player_id group by t2.player_id

select * from organizations as t1 join organization_contact_individuals as t2 on t1.organization_id = t2.organization_id join individuals as t3 on t2.individual_id = t3.individual_id where t1.organization_name = " labour party "
select organisations.* from organisations join organisations_types on organisations.organisation_type_code = organisations_types.code where organisations_types.code ! = ' ed901 '

select organisation_details , count ( organisation_details ) from grants as t1 join organisations as t2 on t1.organisation_id = t2.organisation_id group by organisation_details order by organisation_details asc

select t2.organisation_details , t1.organisation_id from grants as t1 join organisations as t2 on t1.organisation_id = t2.organisation_id group by t2.organisation_details order by t1.organisation_id asc
select t2.organisation_id from grants as t1 join organisations as t2 on t1.organisation_id = t2.organisation_id group by t2.organisation_id having sum ( t1.grant_amount ) < 3000 ;

select t1.organization_name from organizations as t1 join organization_contact_individuals as t2 on t1.organization_id = t2.organization_id group by t1.organization_name order by count ( * ) desc limit 1
select teams.fifa_id , teams_attributes.* from teams_attributes join teams on teams_attributes.team_id = teams.id where teams.long_name = ' rc deportivo de la coruña '
select teams.id , teams_attributes.build_up_play_passing , teams_attributes.build_up_play_positioning_class from teams_attributes join teams on teams_attributes.team_id = teams.id
select max ( teams_attributes.build_up_play_passing ) from teams_attributes join teams on teams_attributes.team_id = teams.id where teams.short_name like ' % stk % '
select t2.location from player as t1 join school as t2 on t1.school_id = t2.school_id group by t1.school_id having count ( * ) > 1
select t2.school from player as t1 join school as t2 on t1.school_id = t2.school_id group by t1.school_id order by count ( * ) asc limit 1 ;
select t1.team , t2.location from player as t1 join school as t2 on t1.school_id = t2.school_id
select t2.denomination from player as t1 join school as t2 on t1.school_id = t2.school_id group by t1.school_id order by count ( * ) desc limit 1
select t3.player_name , t2.coach_name from player_coach as t1 join coach as t2 on t1.coach_id = t2.coach_id join player as t3 on t1.player_id = t3.player_id order by t3.votes desc
select t3.player_name , t2.coach_name from player_coach as t1 join coach as t2 on t1.coach_id = t2.coach_id join player as t3 on t1.player_id = t3.player_id where t1.starting_year < 2012
select t2.coach_name from player_coach as t1 join coach as t2 on t1.coach_id = t2.coach_id join player as t3 on t1.player_id = t3.player_id where t3.player_name = ' ross eadie '
select * from train_station as t1 join station as t2 on t1.station_id = t2.station_id group by t1.station_id order by count ( * ) desc limit 1
select t4.station_id from train_station as t3 join station as t4 on t3.station_id = t4.station_id where t4.location = " london "
select t2.station_id from train_station as t1 join station as t2 on t1.station_id = t2.station_id group by t1.station_id order by count ( * ) desc limit 1
select t2.name from train_station as t1 join station as t2 on t1.station_id = t2.station_id group by t1.station_id having count ( * ) > = 2
select t2.name from train_station as t1 join station as t2 on t1.station_id = t2.station_id group by t1.station_id order by count ( * ) desc limit 1
select * from train_station as t1 join station as t2 on t1.station_id = t2.station_id join train as t3 on t3.train_id = t1.train_id where t1.station_id = 1

select t3.name , t3.time from train_station as t1 join station as t2 on t1.station_id = t2.station_id join train as t3 on t3.train_id = t1.train_id where t2.location = ' london ' order by t3.time desc
select draft_details from document_drafts where document_id = 7
select * from draft_copies ;
select document_id , count ( * ) from draft_copies group by document_id order by draft_number desc limit 1 ;
select t3.name , t3.time from station as t1 join route as t2 on t1.id = t2.station_id join train as t3 on t2.train_id = t3.id where t1.local_authority = " chiltern "
select coach_name from coach as t1 join player_coach as t2 on t1.coach_id = t2.coach_id where starting_year = 2010
select t2.type , count ( * ) from school_bus as t1 join school as t2 on t1.school_id = t2.school_id group by t2.type
select type , count ( * ) from school_bus as t1 join school as t2 on t1.school_id = t2.school_id group by t2.type order by count ( * ) asc
select gname from plays_games as t1 join video_games as t2 on t1.gameid = t2.gameid group by t1.gameid
select gname from plays_games as t1 join video_games as t2 on t1.gameid = t2.gameid group by t1.gameid order by sum ( hours_played ) desc
select t2.team_id , avg ( t1.attendance ) from home_game as t1 join team as t2 on t1.team_id = t2.team_id where t1.year = 2013 group by t1.team_id
select sum ( t1.attendance ) from home_game as t1 join team as t2 on t1.team_id = t2.team_id_br where t2.name = ' cleveland forest citys '
select t2.name from home_game as t1 join team as t2 on t1.team_id = t2.team_id_br where t1.year = 1980 order by t1.attendance asc limit 1 ;
select sum ( t1.attendance ) from home_game as t1 join team as t2 on t1.team_id = t2.team_id_br where t2.name = ' boston red stockings ' and t1.year = 2005 ;
select sum ( t1.attendance ) from home_game as t1 join team as t2 on t1.team_id = t2.team_id_br where t1.year = 1871
select count ( * ) from salary as t1 join player as t2 on t1.player_id = t2.player_id join team as t3 on t3.team_id_br = t1.team_id where t3.name = ' washington nationals '

select t2.name_first , t2.name_last , t2.name_given from salary as t1 join player as t2 on t1.player_id = t2.player_id join team as t3 on t3.team_id_br = t1.team_id where t1.year = 2007 and t3.name = 'washington nationals'
select t2.name_first , t2.name_last from salary as t1 join player as t2 on t1.player_id = t2.player_id join team as t3 on t3.team_id_br = t1.team_id where t1.year = 2005 or t1.year = 2007

select t2.name_first , t2.name_last from salary as t1 join player as t2 on t1.player_id = t2.player_id join team as t3 on t3.team_id_br = t1.team_id where t3.name = ' washington nationals ' group by t2.player_id
select years_played , count ( years_played ) from player as t1 join team as t2 on t1.team = t2.team_id where t2.name = " columbus crew " group by years_played
select count ( * ) from team_franchise as team_franchisealias0 where team_franchisealias0.active = " var0 " ;
